law.history: Repealed 1956 Ky. Acts ch. 101, sec. 34. -- Amended 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 96, secs. 8 and 9. -- Recodified 1942 Ky. Acts ch. 208, sec. 1, effective October 1, 1942, from Ky. Stat. sec. 979b-8.

metadata.catchline-at-repeal: Arrest for violation of probation; revocation on commission of subsequent offense.
